The paper deals with decidability properties of regular graph constraints, which are related to typestate checking and shape analysis techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the reduction of regular graph constraints to automata and tiling problems, which are topics that fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories, respectively. The paper also mentions the use of regular graph constraints in three-valued logic and invariant checking, which are relevant to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories, respectively.
